<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 8:59AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Pittsburg County through 930 AM CDT...
At 859 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
southeast of Wardville, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and dime to penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Kiowa...                          Blanco...
Pittsburg...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
